column140: Drop-Seq was performed following the protocol as previously described (Macosko et al., 2015). Briefly, three pump-controlled syringes with cell suspension (200,000 cells/mL), barcoded beads in lysis buffer (200,000 beads/mL), and droplet generation oil were connected to a microfluidic device under microscope supervision. During droplets generation, the cell and bead flow speed was set at 4,000uL/hr, and the oil speed at 15,000uL/hr. The droplets were collected into 50mL falcon tubes (usually less than 5mL). Following droplet breakage, we performed 1st strand cDNA synthesis on beads following the SMART-PCR protocol (Macosko et al., 2015). Finally, the resulting full-length cDNA library was prepared for sequencing.
